This paper deals with analyzing online petition signature data and inferring virality and diffusion structure. The paper discusses measures based on temporal dynamics and simulations for a theoretical model, which are relevant to social media and network analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Additionally, the paper discusses threshold effects and simulations, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of signature data for inferring virality, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
